regularly command four-figure premiums on the secondary market, making savvy buying more important than ever."}]]}],["$","section","1",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-poppins, Poppins, sans-serif)","fontSize":"20px","fontWeight":700,"color":"#0f172a","marginBottom":"12px","lineHeight":1.3,"paddingBottom":"10px","borderBottom":"2px solid #f1f5f9"},"children":"Which Platforms Offer the Best Value Right Now"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"15px","lineHeight":1.9,"color":"#475569","margin":0},"children":"Our latest price analysis across StubHub, Viagogo, Ticketmaster Resale, and SeatPick shows that prices for the same seat can differ by up to 35%. SeatPick consistently aggregates the lowest verified listings for mid-table fixtures, while StubHub tends to edge ahead on elite six-fixture games where its buyer-guarantee attracts premium sellers. For fans on a tighter budget, setting up price-drop alerts on Ticketmaster Resale for dates six to eight weeks out remains one of the most reliable strategies."}]]}],["$","section","2",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-poppins, Poppins, sans-serif)","fontSize":"20px","fontWeight":700,"color":"#0f172a","marginBottom":"12px","lineHeight":1.3,"paddingBottom":"10px","borderBottom":"2px solid #f1f5f9"},"children":"How to Time Your Purchase for Maximum Savings"}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"15px","lineHeight":1.9,"color":"#475569","margin":0},"children":"Data from the last three seasons reveals a clear pricing pattern: tickets typically peak in the 48-hour window immediately after fixtures are announced, drop by roughly 15% in the following fortnight, and then spike again in the final 72 hours before kick-off as sellers panic-sell. The sweet spot for most fixtures is three to four weeks before match day. Midweek fixtures almost always come in cheaper than weekend equivalents even when the two teams are identical, so flexibility with travel is a real advantage."}]]}